</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1399,489,656]" pageId="11" pageNumber="81">
As 
<taxonomicName authority="Houben, Proesmans &amp; Artois" authorityName="Houben, Proesmans &amp; Artois" authorityYear="2022" box="[229,802,489,515]" family="Typhloplanidae" genus="Bryoplana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="11" pageNumber="81" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="belgica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[229,449,489,515]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="81">Bryoplana belgica</emphasis>
Houben, Proesmans &amp; Artois
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[810,901,489,515]" pageId="11" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is only the second species to be described within the genus, we here provide a new, emended diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Steenkiste, Davison &amp; Artois, 2010" authorityName="Van Steenkiste, Davison &amp; Artois" authorityYear="2010" family="Typhloplanidae" genus="Bryoplana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="11" pageNumber="81" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[949,1074,524,550]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="81">Bryoplana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Van Steenkiste N. &amp; Davison P. &amp; Artois T." pageId="11" pageNumber="81" pagination="285 - 291" refId="ref16235" refString="Van Steenkiste N., Davison P. &amp; Artois T. 2010. Bryoplana xerophila n. g. n. sp., a new limnoterrestrial microturbellarian (Platyhelminthes, Typhloplanidae, Protoplanellinae) from epilithic mosses, with notes on its ecology. Zoological Science 27 (3): 285 - 291. https: // doi. org / 10.2108 / zsj. 27.285" type="journal article" year="2010">Van Steenkiste, Davison &amp; Artois, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as the 
<typeStatus box="[517,568,560,586]" pageId="11" pageNumber="81">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Steenkiste, Davison &amp; Artois, 2010" authorityName="Van Steenkiste, Davison &amp; Artois" authorityYear="2010" box="[668,1394,559,586]" family="Typhloplanidae" genus="Bryoplana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="11" pageNumber="81" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="xerophila">
<emphasis box="[668,914,559,585]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="81">Bryoplana xerophila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Van Steenkiste N. &amp; Davison P. &amp; Artois T." box="[921,1394,559,586]" pageId="11" pageNumber="81" pagination="285 - 291" refId="ref16235" refString="Van Steenkiste N., Davison P. &amp; Artois T. 2010. Bryoplana xerophila n. g. n. sp., a new limnoterrestrial microturbellarian (Platyhelminthes, Typhloplanidae, Protoplanellinae) from epilithic mosses, with notes on its ecology. Zoological Science 27 (3): 285 - 291. https: // doi. org / 10.2108 / zsj. 27.285" type="journal article" year="2010">Van Steenkiste, Davison &amp; Artois, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. For further details, please refer to the discussion on 
<taxonomicName authority="Houben, Proesmans &amp; Artois" authorityName="Houben, Proesmans &amp; Artois" authorityYear="2022" box="[818,1297,594,621]" family="Typhloplanidae" genus="Bryoplana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="11" pageNumber="81" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="belgica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[818,940,594,620]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="81">B. belgica</emphasis>
Houben, Proesmans &amp; Artois
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1306,1399,595,621]" pageId="11" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
below.
</paragraph>
